Mini-Datafest: Airbnbeantown

R Workshop

June 9, 2016

For this activity you’ll be investigating a data set that contains information from all listings on airbnb for Boston as they appeared on October 3rd, 2015.

Data

To download the compressed .csv file, click the link below:

https://www.dropbox.com/s/xk6e3hrfh4qiw3w/listings.csv.gz?dl=0

Objective

Your job is simple (?): use the data available to gain insight into the process of the hoteling and the sharing economy. Your final product will be four slides (feel free to use markdown ioslides, R presentations, keynote, google slides, etc.).

A suggested strategy is the following:

  • Get the lay of the land by getting a sense of the data available and doing exploratory data analysis.
  • Identify the 1-3 topics/questions that you find most interesting.
  • Formulate a possible visualization/statistic/ranking that will address the questions.
  • Diagram a pathway to get from the raw data to the final data product.
